ex.chText: 他的鞋过时了。
ex.enText: His shoes were out of fashion.

ex.chText: 今年又流行长卷发了。
ex.enText: Long and curly hair is in fashion again this year.

synonyms.bx: 指某一时期服装、发型等的时兴式样。

ex.chText: 一种文风
ex.enText: a literary mode

ex.chText: 她总是很了解服装的最新流行款式。
ex.enText: She always understands well the newest mode in dresses.

synonyms.bx: 指文学、艺术等的风格或服装等的式样。

ex.chText: 这些房间是以传统风格装修的。
ex.enText: The rooms are decorated in the traditional style.

ex.chText: 过去10年里，汽车款式在全球范围内变化很大。
ex.enText: Car styles around the whole world have changed a lot in the past decade.

ex.chText: 长裙子不流行了。
ex.enText: Long skirts are out of style.

synonyms.bx: 指服装、发型、家具等的设计款式，也可指流行的式样。

ex.chText: 他的教学方法很传统。
ex.enText: His teaching method is quite traditional.

ex.chText: 这是中国学生学好英语的一种有效的方法。
ex.enText: This is an effective method for Chinese students to learn English well.

synonyms.bx: 指有计划地做某事的方法，尤指很多人都知道并使用的方法。

ex.chText: 他的新英语教学法很受学生欢迎。
ex.enText: His new approach to teaching English was very popular among the students.

ex.chText: 你为什么不采用传统的艺术评论方法呢？
ex.enText: Why don't you take a traditional approach to art criticism?

synonyms.bx: 指行事或处理问题的方法，常后接介词 to 。

ex.chText: 他像往常那样结束了讲话。
ex.enText: He finished the speech in his usual manner.

ex.chText: 他以这种方式死去，使得该事件更加复杂了。
ex.enText: The manner of his death made the matter more complicated.

synonyms.bx: 指做某事或某事发生的方式，通常只用单数。

ex.chText: 这是他们唯一的交流方式。
ex.enText: This is their only means of communication.

ex.chText: 体罚不应该作为约束儿童的手段。
ex.enText: Physical punishment should not be used as a means of controlling children.

synonyms.bx: 指做某事或为达到某种目的而采用的方法或手段。

ex.chText: 他们有不同的思维方式。
ex.enText: They have different modes of thought.

ex.chText: 她当时期待着过一种悠闲的生活。
ex.enText: She was looking forward to a relaxed mode of life.

synonyms.bx: 指行为、生活或做某事的方式，多因习惯、传统或习俗而形成，有时含刻板之意。

ex.chText: 你处理这个问题的方式是什么？
ex.enText: What is your way to tackle this problem?

ex.chText: 游泳是减肥的一种方式。
ex.enText: Swimming is one way to lose weight.

ex.chText: 他用他自己的方式爱她。
ex.enText: He loved her in his own way.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，可指做某事或达成某事的方法，也可指某事发生的方式。

tr: how something is done or how it happens
example: in the characteristic New York style

tr: the most frequent value of a random variable
any of various fixed orders of the various diatonic notes within an octave
verb inflections that express how the action or state is conceived by the speaker
a classification of propositions on the basis of whether they claim necessity or possibility or impossibility
a particular functioning condition or arrangement
example: switched from keyboard to voice mode

value.def: A mode of life or behaviour is a particular way of living or behaving.

example.ex: He switched automatically into interview mode.
example.tran: 他自动切换到访谈模式。

value.def: A mode is a particular style in art, literature, or dress.

example.ex: ...a slightly more elegant and formal mode of dress...
example.tran: 略显典雅和正式的着装风格

example.ex: Levi is best known for work in a very different mode from what is to be found here.
example.tran: 利瓦伊最为人所知之处在于他的工作风格同这里的人迥然不同。

value.def: On some cameras or electronic devices, the different modes available are the different programs or settings that you can choose when you use them.

example.ex: ...when the camera is in manual mode.
example.tran: 当相机处于手动拍摄模式的时候

value.tran: (照相机、电子设备的)模式，状态
